2022 is over, the heavy reality of a 28 week touring schedule within a year sets in after getting a 1.5 year break from it. It’s all been rewarding and worthwhile and the victories have been immense and beyond what I thought was possible. The hardships and sacrifices that come with it are sad, they’re stressful, and they are not over. I’m blessed to have gotten engaged to my soulmate this year and to be able to see more measurable progress in everything I’m a part of. To my friends making sacrifices too, please push through with me and we will enjoy our wins together as they come. Happy new year to all 🤘🏻

Song: @currents - The Death We Seek

It’s the first single, it’s the name of the album, and most importantly… it’s a good time. This song was the product of a crazy experiment using Solemn Tones Odin to program out the whole song (MIDI Guitars) to write the demo back somewhere over two years ago. I had never done it before and I haven’t done it since but it was fun to try before recording the guitars for real later on. I was a little sneaky and pitch shift the octave in the first section to make some higher notes happen in classic “Look ma, one hand!” fashion.

Currents album “The Death We Seek” is our May 5th!

“The Death We Seek” is here! 

It’s been 3 years since the last record already and much of that time was spent stuck at home writing. A lot of weird stuff was made in that time but we’re very pleased with the ten core songs that made it to the end. @brianwille turned everything up to the next level, the ideas and skills he brought to the table this time still blow me away, I can’t wait to see what comes next. I finally got to do vocals on a @currents song, immensely grateful to the guys for believing in me. 

Big thank you to our ever-growing team and community of supporters, next week we start our first cross-country headline tour and it is going to be IMMENSE. We’ll see you soon 🌙

Ten years ago I was asked to start working with the Connecticut band Currents and write their album with them. That same week, I recorded a body of music to be released under the name “Shadow of Intent”. The two carried on for the next ten years, carving a place in the music industry, and I have been fortunate enough to serve as the guitarist and songwriter for both. For me, this is a 10th anniversary celebration for everything we’ve gotten to do.

January 27th we take both bands and Co-Headline Webster Theater in Hartford, along with our fellow New Englanders Boundaries and Fuming Mouth. I’ll be playing two fifty minute back-to-back sets and both bands will be doing a Q&A/Signing/Hangout for all VIPs. See you there!
